<subSubSection pageId="84" pageNumber="85" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="84.[151,1437,690,1615]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1410,1435]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1966" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1966" box="[680,957,1410,1435]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripes">
<emphasis box="[680,806,1411,1435]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">A. nigripes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[816,957,1410,1435]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refId="ref280374" refString="Evans, H. E. (1966) A revision of the genus Anisepyris Kieffer (Hymenoptera. Bethylidae). Studia Entomologica, 9, 1 - 120." type="journal article">Evans, 1966</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by having the head distinctly wider than long; the mandible wide apically and angulate; the clypeus with apical margin truncate and rounded; the antennal scrobe ecarinate; the frons with a short frontal line; and the pronotal disc with a single median fovea, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1966" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">A. nigripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the head wide; the mandible narrow, slightly angled, and with the lower tooth longer than others; the clypeus rounded, short, and with an apical median tooth; the antennal scrobe carinate; the frons without a short frontal line; and the pronotal disc without a fovea.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
